sources.title: Sea Racketeers
sources.description: J. Carrol Naish plays a slimy villain again; this time he's running a casino on a ship and smuggling furs past the Coast Guard.

sources.title: Sea Racketeers (1937) CRIME THRILLER
sources.description:
Stars: Weldon Heyburn, Jeanne Madden, Warren Hymer
 Director: Hamilton MacFadden

 A courageous Coast Guard officer he takes on a gang of seafaring crooks who use a floating casino as a cover for their piratical activities! J. Carroll Naish plays Durant, head of the modern-day buccaneers.

metadata.Plot: Step back in time to the golden age of classic crime movies. The arch villain (played by J. Carrol Naish) is running a casino on board a ship. At the same time he&#xFFFD;&#x6EA;s smuggling illegal furs right past the Coast Guard. Can the authorities catch him out? A classic film directed by Hamilton MacFadden.
